going to do now is to find

00:01:09.410 --> 00:01:15.430 position:56%
out about all the things that you've
been up to since then [laughter],

00:01:15.430 --> 00:01:19.210
which would probably
take us about a year and.

00:01:19.210 --> 00:01:25.900
But to begin with, I
remember that one of the thing

00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:30.920
that we did together was a concert
at, in the garden at the Museum

00:01:30.920 --> 00:01:33.100
of Modern Art in New York.

00:01:33.100 --> 00:01:37.370
And that was a great evening,

00:01:37.370 --> 00:01:41.350
and I'm sure that you remember
a little bit about that.

00:01:41.350 --> 00:01:42.920
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Yes, I do.

00:01:42.920 --> 00:01:47.480
And Dan, thank you.

00:01:47.480 --> 00:01:53.390
It's great to see you again,
and you are looking very well.

00:01:53.390 --> 00:01:57.350
Always fond memories, and
my deepest appreciation

00:01:57.350 --> 00:02:00.700
because when I first
came to New York,

00:02:00.700 --> 00:02:06.350
you really supported
me like 100 percent.

00:02:06.350 --> 00:02:14.290
And I'll always remember
that, very, very kind of you.

00:02:14.290 --> 00:02:19.690
I remember this concert
very vaguely [laughter].

00:02:19.690 --> 00:02:23.340
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: Yeah, it
was with the Choir of Lancaster.

00:02:23.340 --> 00:02:24.820
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim:
Oh [inaudible], yeah!

00:02:24.820 --> 00:02:27.340
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: And
Morris [assumed spelling],

00:02:27.340 --> 00:02:35.320
