00:05:04.960 --> 00:05:08.020
often, I guess, and he
played it beautifully.

00:05:08.020 --> 00:05:11.200
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Incredible,
incredible, wonderful player.

00:05:11.200 --> 00:05:21.350 position:56%
And also Cliff Guyton, flute player,
cello, and clarinet, and piccolo.

00:05:21.350 --> 00:05:25.420
The cello and bass
player, Noah Jackson,

00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:27.880
this is his first gig
out of college.

00:05:27.880 --> 00:05:29.180
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: Really?

00:05:29.180 --> 00:05:33.860
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: He came out
of college last year and joined us,

00:05:33.860 --> 00:05:40.790
and quite, I think there's
a, the younger generation of,

00:05:40.790 --> 00:05:47.620
of musicians who, technically
skilled, but also have the passion,

00:05:47.620 --> 00:05:51.270
and also lock into the tradition.

00:05:51.270 --> 00:05:54.070
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: Well he's a
fine cellist and it's interesting.

00:05:54.070 --> 00:05:58.040
Again, usually when the
cello was used in jazz,

00:05:58.040 --> 00:06:01.140
it was pizzicato, [inaudible].

00:06:01.140 --> 00:06:03.500
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim:
[inaudible] yeah.

00:06:03.500 --> 00:06:05.360
Yeah, Kello Scott [assumed
spelling] at that time told me,

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:10.060
he said he'd play it amplified.

00:06:10.060 --> 00:06:15.870
He amplified the cello and slung
it, and then stood up with it.

00:06:15.870 --> 00:06:19.010
So I ask him to tell
me, why do you do this?

00:06:19.010 --> 00:06:22.700
And he said, "I wanted to get
away from the drummer" [laughter].

00:06:22.700 --> 00:06:32.330
Because the only place you're right
to the drummer and amplify it.

00:06:32.330 --> 00:06:36.460
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: I saw Kello, I
think not with you unfortunately,

00:06:36.460 --> 00:06:40.530
but I saw him live
once at the Half Note,

00:06:40.530 --> 00:06:43.650
which was a nice club in downtown.

00:06:43.650 --> 00:06:46.440
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Yeah,
I remember the Half Note.

00:06:46.440 --> 00:06:48.580
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: They
had very good food too,

00:06:48.580 --> 00:06:50.390
which was unusual [inaudible]

00:06:50.390 --> 00:06:54.860
At the Velvet Shrinegard
[phonetic], they had nothing.

00:06:54.860 --> 00:06:57.280
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Exactly.

