spelling] introduced me

00:07:48.410 --> 00:07:55.360
to [inaudible], who was the
manager of the Chelsea Hotel,

00:07:55.360 --> 00:08:04.920
and that's where we stayed
at a colony of artists.

00:08:04.920 --> 00:08:09.010
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: Yes, the
Chelsea was a famous hotel on 23rd.

00:08:09.010 --> 00:08:10.310
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim:
23rd street, yeah.

00:08:10.310 --> 00:08:15.520
But before it was because the
children had to go to school,

00:08:15.520 --> 00:08:22.030
it was a walk away, anywhere that
you wanted to go, you want to go

00:08:22.030 --> 00:08:24.050
down to the village, yeah.

00:08:24.050 --> 00:08:26.280
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: That's a good
location, and then as you say,

00:08:26.280 --> 00:08:28.350
you know, a lot of
artists lived there.

00:08:28.350 --> 00:08:29.650
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Yeah.

00:08:29.650 --> 00:08:30.950
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern:
Interesting people.

00:08:30.950 --> 00:08:33.380
And it was more or less
of a residential hotel.

00:08:33.380 --> 00:08:34.680
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: It
was residential, yeah.

00:08:34.680 --> 00:08:40.540
And then a few years, over two or
three years ago, it all changed

00:08:40.540 --> 00:08:43.650
when it changed ownership.

00:08:43.650 --> 00:08:52.160
Yeah so then, we had to move out.

00:08:55.450 --> 00:08:58.090
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: But then,

00:08:58.090 --> 00:09:03.200
it took some time before
you went back home.

00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:08.710
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Yeah,
I went back shortly in 70,

00:09:08.710 --> 00:09:17.440
74 and then it became like most,
for most of us during that time,

00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:19.660
it became totally unbearable.

00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:22.740
Because it was very,
very suppressive.

00:09:22.740 --> 00:09:28.800
And then we left, and
then didn't return

00:09:28.800 --> 00:09:36.340
until Mandela was released
from prison in 98.

00:09:36.340 --> 00:09:38.270
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern:
And you performed

00:09:38.270 --> 00:09:41.000
at Nelson Mandela's inauguration.

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:42.300
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Yeah.

00:09:42.300 --> 00:09:43.600
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern:
What was that like?

00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:46.450
That must have been special.

00:09:46.450 --> 00:09:53.010
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Thing that
I remember most that we had this,

00:09:53.010 --> 00:09:57.870
it was only like unconscious fear

00:09:57.870 --> 00:09:59.770
that we were not supposed
to be there, you know?

00:09:59.770 --> 00:10:03.430
Because it happens to
all of us, so suddenly.

00:10:03.430 --> 00:10:09.380
A place like Pretoria, where you'll
even be weary during those years

00:10:09.380 --> 00:10:12.440
to walk, to walk the streets.

00:10:12.440 --> 00:10:19.830
And it was, it was exhilarating
and it was something confusing also

00:10:19.830 --> 00:10:22.830
because it was too much
to handle [laughter].

00:10:22.830 --> 00:10:24.760 position:56%
Too much to handle at the same time,

00:10:24.760 --> 00:10:29.500
but the inauguration was very
remarkable because there were close

00:10:29.500 --> 00:10:32.350
to a million people
at the Union Building.

00:10:32.350 --> 00:10:37.410
So we never could go, I never went.

00:10:37.410 --> 00:10:45.620
And for me, I mean, it went
on for hours and hours,

00:10:45.620 --> 00:10:51.080
I met all the musicians and
other artists who performed.

00:10:51.080 --> 00:10:58.410
But the display was incredible,
because it was a military display

00:10:58.410 --> 00:11:04.860
of strength, and just to
see how they then managed

00:11:04.860 --> 00:11:10.420
to handle this transition
without major conflict.

00:11:13.910 --> 00:11:17.060
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: Yeah well there
have been some tremendous changes

00:11:17.060 --> 00:11:20.110
there over your lifetime.

00:11:20.110 --> 00:11:21.410
&gt;&gt; Abdullah Ibrahim: Yes.

00:11:21.410 --> 00:11:28.880
Those are, we always
understood that the period

00:11:28.880 --> 00:11:35.720
after the change would
be very, very difficult.

00:11:35.720 --> 00:11:44.560
And there's some of the
problems that we face now.

00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:48.590
Because in some ways, we were not,

00:11:48.590 --> 00:11:56.820
we didn't prepare ourselves
to handle it properly.

00:11:56.820 --> 00:12:04.020
But I'm quite amazing, in
spite of all the negativity,

00:12:04.020 --> 00:12:08.740
there are people there
who are unsung

00:12:10.020 --> 00:12:14.380
and working behind the
scenes, very dedicated,

00:12:14.380 --> 00:12:20.200 position:56%
and also very knowledgeable, and
also have the vision for the people.

00:12:20.200 --> 00:12:26.190
So we are, we're hopeful.

00:12:26.190 --> 00:12:31.320
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: You make
your home now in Cape Town,

00:12:31.320 --> 00:12:36.610
