for example, with a group,

00:16:57.660 --> 00:17:03.060
I suggest to the sound engineers
that we first play acoustically.

00:17:03.060 --> 00:17:07.850 position:56%
And we can hear each other on stage,
and then transport this into the,

00:17:07.850 --> 00:17:11.220
you know, into the whole And
[inaudible] sense of technique

00:17:11.220 --> 00:17:13.430
that I can, I can actually hear,

00:17:13.430 --> 00:17:17.600
at what level of volume I should
strike the note for it to reach,

00:17:17.600 --> 00:17:21.570
you know, to fill the space.

00:17:21.570 --> 00:17:22.870
&gt;&gt; Dan Morgenstern: Well,

00:17:22.870 --> 00:17:28.070
it's started with so much music
is over-amplified these days.

00:17:28.070 --> 00:17:36.010
And unnecessarily, I mean
there are clubs in New York

00:17:36.010 --> 00:17:44.320
where you could hear perfectly
well without, you know,

00:17:44.320 --> 00:17:47.740
having a bunch of microphones
on stage.

00:17:47.740 --> 00:17:54.220
But they always put them there,
and once they amplify the drums,

00:17:54.220 --> 00:18:00.440
then they have to amplify
everything else [laughter].

